# ✅ Example Usage — Multi Query Case

```python
plan = {
    "execution_mode": "multi",
    "queries": [
        {
            "keywords": ["productivity suite features"],
            "filters": {
                "space": None,
                "author": None,
                "content_type": "page",
                "labels": None,
                "date_from": None,
                "date_to": None,
                "title": None
            },
            "sort": {"field": None, "order": None}
        },
        {
            "keywords": ["productivity suite software development life cycle"],
            "filters": {
                "space": None,
                "author": None,
                "content_type": "page",
                "labels": None,
                "date_from": None,
                "date_to": None,
                "title": None
            },
            "sort": {"field": None, "order": None}
        }
    ]
}

cql_queries = MultiQueryCQLGenerator.generate(plan)

for q in cql_queries:
    print(q)
```

### Output:

```sql
type = "page" AND text ~ "\"productivity suite features\""

type = "page" AND text ~ "\"productivity suite software development life cycle\""
```

